gov.usgs.traveltime

Class TtRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.traveltime.TtRequest

  • public class TtRequest
extends java.lang.Object
    Request a set of travel times or plot data within the current session. An object of this type should be passed to the tau-p package for each user request for travel-time points or curves.
    Author:
    Ray

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      TtRequest(SessionRequest source)
      The session request will be needed for source-receiver calculations and to cross check that the right information is available.

    • Method Detail

      • simple

        public void simple(double delta,
                   double stationElev)
        Request a set of travel times by distance. Only the elevation correction is added.
        Parameters:
        delta - Source-receiver distance in degrees.
        stationElev - Receiver elevation relative to WGS84 in kilometers.

      • full

        public void full(double delta,
                 double stationLat,
                 double stationLon,
                 double stationElev)
        Request a set of travel times by station coordinates. In this case, ellipticity and bounce point corrections will be added to the travel time results as well as the elevation correction.
        Parameters:
        delta - Source-receiver distance in degrees (optional).
        stationLat - Geographical receiver latitude in degrees.
        stationLon - Geographical receiver longitude in degrees.
        stationElev - Receiver elevation relative to WGS84 in kilometers.
